Class title: Fresh vegetables (except potatoes and pulse crops)
Class definition: This class comprises fresh vegetables, except potatoes and pulse crops. Vegetables are temporary crops cultivated principally for human consumption both as field crops and garden crops, in the open and under protective cover. Certain gramineous and leguminous plants, if harvested while green for their green grains or for their green pods (for example, green peas, string beans, green maize) are treated as fresh vegetables, but if harvested for their dry grains or seeds, are classified as cereals and pulse crops.

Class definition: This group comprises natural gas liquids (NGLs) and related products. NGLs are found in natural gas and include liquefied petroleum gases or LPGs (propane, butane), ethane, lease condensate, pentanes plus, among others.

Class definition: This class comprises natural gas liquids (NGLs) and related products. NGLs are found in natural gas and include liquefied petroleum gases or LPGs (propane, butane), ethane, lease condensate, pentanes plus, among others.
This subclass comprises liquefied petroleum gases (LPGs) consisting primarily of propane and butane.

Normally straight-chain gaseous paraffinic (saturated) hydrocarbon or compound (C3H8) extracted from natural gas or refinery gas streams. It is a colourless gas that boils at a temperature of -42° Celsius. Cover propane mixes.

Normally straight-chain or branch-chain gaseous paraffinic hydrocarbon (C4H10) extracted from natural gas or refinery gas streams. It is a colourless gas that boils at a temperature of -1° Celsius. Covers butane mixes.
This subclass comprises natural gas liquids, except liquefied petroleum gases (LPGs), and covers lease condensate and pentanes plus.
Straight-chain gaseous paraffinic (saturated) hydrocarbon (C2H6) extracted predominantly from natural gas streams. It is a colourless gas that boils at a temperature of -88° Celsius.

Light liquid hydrocarbons recovered from lease separators or field facilities at associated and non-associated natural gas wells. Mostly pentanes and heavier hydrocarbons. Normally enter the crude oil stream after production.

Mixture of mainly pentanes and heavier hydrocarbons that ordinarily contains butanes. Pentanes plus (also known as natural gasoline) is obtained from the processing of raw gas, condensate or crude oil.

This group comprises coal, a combustible black (hard coal) and brownish-black (brown coal) rock consisting of more than 50 percent by weight and more than 70 percent by volume of carbonaceous material. It is formed from plant remains that have been compacted, hardened and chemically altered, and metamorphosed by heat and pressure over geologic time.

This class comprises black coal ranked as hard coal, which includes anthracite and bituminous coal. Hard coal refers to coal of gross calorific value equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis and with a mean random reflectance of vitrinite of at least 0.6 percent.

This subclass comprises anthracite, a high rank hard, lustrous black coal destined primarily for residential and industrial (as steel making) or commercial applications. It has generally less than 10 percent volatile matter and a high carbon content (about 90 percent fixed carbon). Its gross calorific value is equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis.

High rank hard lustrous black coal destined primarily for residential and industrial (as steel making) or commercial applications. It has generally less than 10 percent volatile matter and a high carbon content (about 90 percent fixed carbon). Its gross calorific value is equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis.

This subclass comprises coking or metallurgical coal and other bituminous coal. Bituminous coal is a medium rank coal used for gasification, industrial coking and heat raising, and residential heat raising. It is characterized by higher volatile matter than anthracite (more than 10 percent) and lower carbon content (less than 90 percent fixed carbon). Its gross calorific value is equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis.

Bituminous coal with a quality that allows the production of a coke suitable to support a blast furnace charge. Its gross calorific value is equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis.

Other bituminous coal mainly used for steam raising purposes. It is characterized by higher volatile matter than anthracite (more than 10 percent) and lower carbon content (less than 90 percent fixed carbon). Its gross calorific value is equal to or greater than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis.

This class comprises softer brown coal, which includes sub-bituminous coal and lignite. Brown coal refers to coal of gross calorific value of less than 24,000 kJ/kg, on an ash-free but moist basis, and a mean random reflectance of vitrinite of less than 0.6 percent.

This subclass comprises sub-bituminous coal, a non-agglomerating coal with a gross calorific value equal to or greater than 20,000 kJ/kg and less than 24,000 kJ/kg, containing more than 31 percent volatile matter on a dry mineral matter free basis.

Non-agglomerating coal with a gross calorific value equal to or greater than 20,000 kJ/kg and less than 24,000 kJ/kg, containing more than 31 percent volatile matter on a dry mineral matter free basis.
This subclass comprises lignite, a non-agglomerating coal with a gross calorific value less than 20,000 kJ/kg, containing more than 31 percent volatile matter on a dry mineral matter free basis.
Non-agglomerating coal with a gross calorific value less than 20,000 kJ/kg, containing more than 31 percent volatile matter on a dry mineral matter free basis.

Rental and leasing services of rail equipment with operator or crew, for freight transportation, are included.

This subclass comprises transportation by rail of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods. Class title: Rail freight transportation services (except rental and leasing with operator or crew)

Class definition: Rental or leasing services of locomotives and rail cars, with operator or crew, for transportation of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods.

This class comprises transportation by water of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods. Rental and leasing services of water vessels with operator or crew, for freight transportation, are included.

This subclass comprises transportation by water of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods. Rental and leasing services of water vessels with operator or crew, for freight transportation, are included.

Class title: Water freight transportation services (except rental and leasing with operator or crew)
Class definition: Transportation by water of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods.

Class title: Rental and leasing of freight vessels with operator or crew
Class definition: Rental or leasing services of all types of self-propelled freight vessels for coastal, transoceanic and inland water transport, with operator or crew, for the transportation of bulk liquids and gases in or not in intermodal tank containers; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; climate-controlled or not climate-controlled intermodal containers; automobiles and light-duty trucks; livestock; waste; truck trailers; and all other goods.

This class comprises transportation by air of bulk liquids; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; automobiles and light-duty trucks; and other goods; and transportation of any good into space. Rental and leasing services of cargo or freight aircraft with operator or crew, are included.

This subclass comprises transportation by air of bulk liquids; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; automobiles and light-duty trucks; and other goods; and transportation of any good into space. Rental and leasing services of cargo or freight aircraft with operator or crew, are included.

Class title: Air freight transportation services (except rental and leasing with operator or crew)
Class definition: Transportation by air of bulk liquids; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; automobiles and light-duty trucks; and other goods; and transportation of any good into space.

Class title: Rental and leasing of freight aircraft, with operator or crew
Class definition: Rental or leasing of dedicated cargo or freight aircraft, with operator or crew (''wet leasing'' and ''damp leasing''), for the transportation of bulk liquids; dry bulk not in intermodal containers; climate-control or not climate-control boxed, palletized and other packed goods; automobiles and light-duty trucks; and other goods; and transportation of any good into space. The service may include providing fuel. Renter or lessee generally has operational control of the flight. The period of the rental or lease can go from one month to usually one to two years. Everything less than one month can be considered as ad-hoc charter services.

This class comprises removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of household, office and institutional goods, and goods requiring special handling and protection. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

This subclass comprises removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of personal effects and property to be used in a dwelling. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

Removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of personal effects and property to be used in a dwelling. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

This subclass comprises removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of furniture, fixtures, equipment and other property, but not stock-in-trade, of stores, offices, museums, institutions, hospitals and other establishments. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

Removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of furniture, fixtures, equipment and other property, but not stock-in-trade, of stores, offices, museums, institutions, hospitals and other establishments. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

This subclass comprises removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of goods requiring special handling and protection, such as objects of art, antiques, pianos, displays and exhibits when not part of a household or commercial move. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.

Removing from premises, loading, transporting, unloading and moving into new premises of goods requiring special handling and protection, such as objects of art, antiques, pianos, displays and exhibits when not part of a household or commercial move. Goods are of varying shapes and sizes. Covers moving by all modes of transportation. May include packing and unpacking. May include declared value coverage.
This class comprises the provision of small general-purpose aircraft and helicopters with a crew to perform specialized services.
This subclass comprises the provision of small general-purpose aircraft and helicopters with a crew to perform specialized services.
Provision of small general-purpose aircraft and helicopters with a crew to perform specialized services.
This group comprises postal services; and courier, parcel, and local messenger and delivery services.

This class comprises delivery of letters and parcels under the terms of a universal service obligation, such as an obligation governing delivery by post offices. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

This subclass comprises delivery of letters and parcels under the terms of a universal service obligation, such as an obligation governing delivery by post offices. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Delivery of letters and parcels under the terms of a universal service obligation, such as an obligation governing delivery by post offices. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Class title: Courier, parcel, and local messenger and delivery services
Class definition: This class comprises station-to-station transportation of small packages and documents without tracking; courier and messenger services; and neighbourhood delivery of small purchased items.

Class title: Station-to-station transportation of small packages and documents without tracking
Class definition: This subclass comprises transportation of small packages and documents without tracking of each package and document. Service is typically station-to-station but may be door-to-door. Transportation is provided on passenger buses and trains according to published schedules but departure and arrival times are not guaranteed. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Class title: Station-to-station transportation of small packages and documents without tracking
Class definition: Transportation of small packages and documents without tracking of each package and document. Service is typically station-to-station but may be door-to-door. Transportation is provided on passenger buses and trains according to published schedules but departure and arrival times are not guaranteed. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

This subclass comprises transportation and delivery, by a definite day and possibly by a definite time, of small packages and documents, with tracking of each package and document. Delivery by the scheduled day or specified time may be guaranteed. Small packages usually can be handled by one person without using special equipment. Service is typically door-to-door, although there may be options for the shipper to drop a package off and for the receiver to pick it up, and occasional shippers may have to drop off their packages. Pick-up and delivery outside normal service area or outside normal service hours, and pick-up on demand or on a regular schedule, are covered here. Service may include customs clearance. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Transportation and delivery, on the same day as pick-up and possibly by a definite time, of small packages and documents, with tracking of each package and document. Delivery on the day or by the specified time may be guaranteed. Small packages usually can be handled by one person without using special equipment. Service is typically door-to-door, although there may be options for the shipper to drop a package off and for the receiver to pick it up, and occasional shippers may have to drop off their packages. Pick-up and delivery outside normal service area or outside normal service hours, and pick-up on demand or on a regular schedule, are covered here. Service may include customs clearance. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Transportation and delivery, on the first business day or first calendar day following pick-up, and possibly by a definite time, of small packages and documents, with tracking of each package and document. Delivery by the scheduled day or specified time may be guaranteed. Small packages usually can be handled by one person without using special equipment. Service is typically door-to-door, although there may be options for the shipper to drop a package off and for the receiver to pick it up, and occasional shippers may have to drop off their packages. Pick-up and delivery outside normal service area or outside normal service hours, and pick-up on demand or on a regular schedule, are covered here. Service may include customs clearance. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Class title: Second-day or later courier and messenger services
Class definition: Transportation and delivery, on the second business day or second calendar day following pick-up, or on a later specified day, and possibly by a definite time, of small packages and documents, with tracking of each package and document. Delivery by the scheduled day or specified time may be guaranteed. Small packages usually can be handled by one person without using special equipment. Service is typically door-to-door, although there may be options for the shipper to drop a package off and for the receiver to pick it up, and occasional shippers may have to drop off their packages. Pick-up and delivery outside normal service area or outside normal service hours, and pick-up on demand or on a regular schedule, are covered here. Service may include customs clearance. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service. May include declared value coverage.

Class title: Neighbourhood delivery of small purchased items
Class definition: This subclass comprises door-to-door transportation and delivery of small purchased and serviced items such as take-out meals, groceries, prescription drugs and dry-cleaned clothes. Service is limited to a specified neighbourhood. Delivery is made immediately after the item is purchased or ordered, or scheduled within a short time. Expected delivery time is made known to the recipient. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service.

Class title: Neighbourhood delivery of small purchased items
Class definition: Door-to-door transportation and delivery of small purchased and serviced items such as take-out meals, groceries, prescription drugs and dry-cleaned clothes. Service is limited to a specified neighbourhood. Delivery is made immediately after the item is purchased or ordered, or scheduled within a short time. Expected delivery time is made known to the recipient. May include collect on delivery (C.O.D.) service.

This group comprises urban transit services; taxi and limousine services; interurban and rural bus passenger transportation services; school bus services; other transit and passenger transportation services by road; rail passenger transportation services; water passenger transportation services; air passenger transportation services; and scenic and sightseeing tour services. Rental and leasing services of passenger vehicles with operator, driver or crew are included.

This class comprises passenger transportation operated on a network of regular routes and on regular schedules. Service is centred on an urban area and covers urban and suburban areas and areas from which they draw commuters. Commuter services that primarily carry passengers to and from the urban centre are included. Transportation may involve one or more types of vehicles, such as buses, subways, streetcars, commuter trains and ferries. Passengers are permitted to pay on a per-trip basis, and the fare may be calculated on a zone basis. Covers urban transit services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

This subclass comprises passenger transportation operated on a network of regular routes and on regular schedules. Service is centred on an urban area and covers urban and suburban areas and areas from which they draw commuters. Commuter services that primarily carry passengers to and from the urban centre are included. Transportation may involve one or more types of vehicles, such as buses, subways, streetcars, commuter trains and ferries. Passengers are permitted to pay on a per-trip basis, and the fare may be calculated on a zone basis. Covers urban transit services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Passenger transportation operated on a network of regular routes and on regular schedules. Service is centred on an urban area and covers urban and suburban areas and areas from which they draw commuters. Commuter services that primarily carry passengers to and from the urban centre are included. Transportation may involve one or more types of vehicles, such as buses, subways, streetcars, commuter trains and ferries. Passengers are permitted to pay on a per-trip basis, and the fare may be calculated on a zone basis. Covers urban transit services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.
This class comprises local limousine services; local taxi services and taxi dispatch services.

This subclass comprises local passenger transportation by luxury automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available only by reservation, or without reservation to passengers as they leave an airport or other transportation terminal. In the case of travel from an airport or other transportation terminal, the fee is on the basis of the distance to the destination, calculated on a zone basis; there may be a minimum charge. In other cases, the fee charged is on the basis of the length of time for which the vehicle is reserved; there is normally a minimum length of time and/or a minimum tariff. The vehicle and driver are available to make a series of trips as directed by the customer during the period for which the vehicle has been reserved.

Local passenger transportation by luxury automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available only by reservation, or without reservation to passengers as they leave an airport or other transportation terminal. In the case of travel from an airport or other transportation terminal, the fee is on the basis of the distance to the destination, calculated on a zone basis; there may be a minimum charge. In other cases, the fee charged is on the basis of the length of time for which the vehicle is reserved; there is normally a minimum length of time and/or a minimum tariff. The vehicle and driver are available to make a series of trips as directed by the customer during the period for which the vehicle has been reserved.

Class title: Local taxi services and taxi dispatch services
Class definition: This subclass comprises passenger transportation by automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available on demand. The fee charged to passengers is on the basis of distance travelled. Also comprises taxi dispatch services.
Passenger transportation by automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available on demand. The fee charged to passengers is on the basis of distance travelled.
Taxi dispatch services.

Class title: Interurban and rural bus passenger transportation services
Class definition: This class comprises long distance passenger transportation by road, over fixed routes on a regular schedule. Long distance transportation is generally between metropolitan areas. Service is either part of an interurban network and connecting services to other destinations are available or service is intended to serve a particular destination, and is not designed to connect to a network of interurban service. Covers charges for incidental transportation of passenger baggage.

Class title: Interurban and rural bus passenger transportation services
Class definition: This subclass comprises long distance passenger transportation by road, over fixed routes on a regular schedule. Long distance transportation is generally between metropolitan areas. Service is either part of an interurban network and connecting services to other destinations are available or service is intended to serve a particular destination, and is not designed to connect to a network of interurban service. Covers charges for incidental transportation of passenger baggage.

Class title: Interurban and rural bus passenger transportation services
Class definition: Long distance passenger transportation by road, over fixed routes on a regular schedule. Long distance transportation is generally between metropolitan areas. Service is either part of an interurban network and connecting services to other destinations are available or service is intended to serve a particular destination, and is not designed to connect to a network of interurban service. Covers charges for incidental transportation of passenger baggage.

This class comprises transportation of students between home and school on a regular basis. Service is operated on regular routes and schedules that are designed to accommodate the home locations of individual passengers. The vehicles used are typically buses but may include smaller vehicles such as vans and cars, and may include vehicles accessible to people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids. Passengers are not charged a per-trip fee. Covers school bus services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

This subclass comprises transportation of students between home and school on a regular basis. Service is operated on regular routes and schedules that are designed to accommodate the home locations of individual passengers. The vehicles used are typically buses but may include smaller vehicles such as vans and cars, and may include vehicles accessible to people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids. Passengers are not charged a per-trip fee. Covers school bus services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Transportation of students between home and school on a regular basis. Service is operated on regular routes and schedules that are designed to accommodate the home locations of individual passengers. The vehicles used are typically buses but may include smaller vehicles such as vans and cars, and may include vehicles accessible to people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids. Passengers are not charged a per-trip fee. Covers school bus services whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Class title: Other transit and passenger transportation services by road
Class definition: This class comprises long distance passenger transportation by chartered bus; local passenger transportation by chartered bus; other long distance passenger transportation services by road (except fixed route); shuttle service; other local fixed route passenger transportation service by road; special needs urban transit service; and local shared-ride passenger transportation service. Rental or leasing services of road passenger transportation vehicles with operator or driver are included.

Class title: Long distance passenger transportation by chartered bus
Class definition: This subclass comprises long distance passenger transportation for a specific occasion by road vehicles with sufficient interior height for a person to stand, typically buses but not limousines or taxis, with driver. Service is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only by reservation of the entire vehicle, for which a fee is charged to the party who makes the reservation. The party who makes the reservation may or may not charge the passengers an explicit fee for the transportation. Covers use of vehicles that are accessible to passengers using wheelchairs and other mobility aids.

Class title: Long distance passenger transportation by chartered bus
Class definition: Long distance passenger transportation for a specific occasion by road vehicles with sufficient interior height for a person to stand, typically buses but not limousines or taxis, with driver. Service is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only by reservation of the entire vehicle, for which a fee is charged to the party who makes the reservation. The party who makes the reservation may or may not charge the passengers an explicit fee for the transportation. Covers use of vehicles that are accessible to passengers using wheelchairs and other mobility aids.

Class title: Local passenger transportation by chartered bus
Class definition: This subclass comprises local passenger transportation for a specific occasion by road vehicles with sufficient interior height for a person to stand, typically buses but not limousines or taxis, with driver. Service is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only by reservation of the entire vehicle, for which a fee is charged to the party who makes the reservation. The party who makes the reservation may or may not charge the passengers an explicit fee for the transportation. Covers use of vehicles that are accessible to passengers using wheelchairs and other mobility aids.

Class title: Local passenger transportation by chartered bus
Class definition: Local passenger transportation for a specific occasion by road vehicles with sufficient interior height for a person to stand, typically buses but not limousines or taxis, with driver. Service is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only by reservation of the entire vehicle, for which a fee is charged to the party who makes the reservation. The party who makes the reservation may or may not charge the passengers an explicit fee for the transportation. Covers use of vehicles that are accessible to passengers using wheelchairs and other mobility aids.

Class title: Other long distance passenger transportation services by road (except fixed route)
Class definition: This subclass comprises long distance passenger transportation by luxury automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available only by reservation. The operator carries as many parties having similar origins or destinations as can be accommodated on each trip.

Class title: Other long distance passenger transportation services by road (except fixed route)
Class definition: Long distance passenger transportation by luxury automobile, not operated on regular schedules or routes, and available only by reservation. The operator carries as many parties having similar origins or destinations as can be accommodated on each trip.

This subclass comprises passenger transportation operated on regular routes and on regular schedules or on regular routes on an unscheduled but frequent basis. Service is typically between a limited number of pick-up and drop-off points, with no local service for other points along the route; or on a circular route with frequent stops. The service is not part of a network. As many passengers as can be accommodated are carried on a first-come first-served basis. Passengers may or may not be charged a per-trip fee. Covers shuttle service whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Passenger transportation operated on regular routes and on regular schedules or on regular routes on an unscheduled but frequent basis. Service is typically between a limited number of pick-up and drop-off points, with no local service for other points along the route; or on a circular route with frequent stops. The service is not part of a network. As many passengers as can be accommodated are carried on a first-come first-served basis. Passengers may or may not be charged a per-trip fee. Covers shuttle service whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Class title: Other local fixed route passenger transportation services by road
Class definition: This subclass comprises local fixed route passenger transportation service by road except urban transit service, transportation of students between home and school on a regular basis, and shuttle service. Covers employee transportation to work arranged by the employer and operated on regular routes and schedules. Vehicles used are typically buses but may be smaller vehicles such as vans and cars, and may be accessible to people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids. Passengers are not charged a per-trip fee. Covers employee transportation to work whether paid for by passengers or by contracts. Carpool transportation is provided by arranging and administering pools and providing a vehicle to members of each pool in exchange for a monthly fee to cover operating costs. One or more pool members must act as driver.

Class title: Other local fixed route passenger transportation services by road
Class definition: Local fixed route passenger transportation service by road except urban transit service, transportation of students between home and school on a regular basis, and shuttle service. Covers employee transportation to work arranged by the employer and operated on regular routes and schedules. Vehicles used are typically buses but may be smaller vehicles such as vans and cars, and may be accessible to people using wheelchairs and other mobility aids. Passengers are not charged a per-trip fee. Covers employee transportation to work whether paid for by passengers or by contracts. Carpool transportation is provided by arranging and administering pools and providing a vehicle to members of each pool in exchange for a monthly fee to cover operating costs. One or more pool members must act as driver.

This subclass comprises transportation of passengers who have physical or cognitive impairments that make them unable to use regular urban transit. Transportation is by shared vans, minibuses or automobiles, is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only to registered passengers by reservation. Passengers are transported to and from their individual homes, workplaces and other locations. Passengers are charged a per-trip fee. Covers special needs urban transit service whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

Transportation of passengers who have physical or cognitive impairments that make them unable to use regular urban transit. Transportation is by shared vans, minibuses or automobiles, is not operated on regular schedules or routes, and is available only to registered passengers by reservation. Passengers are transported to and from their individual homes, workplaces and other locations. Passengers are charged a per-trip fee. Covers special needs urban transit service whether paid for by passengers or by contracts.

This subclass comprises local shared-ride service, that is, local shared passenger transportation operated on request, typically between an airport and homes, offices or hotels specified by passengers. The operator carries as many parties having similar origins or destinations as can be accommodated on each trip.

Local shared-ride service, that is, local shared passenger transportation operated on request, typically between an airport and homes, offices or hotels specified by passengers. The operator carries as many parties having similar origins or destinations as can be accommodated on each trip.

Class title: Rental of road passenger transportation vehicles, with operator
Class definition: This subclass comprises rental or operating leasing services of passenger automobiles and light vans with operator or driver, that is, chauffeur-driven car-hire services, wherever delivered, generally supplied on a time basis to a limited number of passengers and frequently involving transportation to more than one destination. Also comprises rental or operating leasing services of buses or coaches with operator or driver for a period of time, not generally dependent on distance. The renter defines how and when the vehicles will be operated, determining schedules, routes, and other operational considerations.

Class title: Rental of passenger automobiles and light vans, with operator
Class definition: Rental or operating leasing services of passenger automobiles and light vans with operator or driver, that is, chauffeur-driven car-hire services, wherever delivered, generally supplied on a time basis to a limited number of passengers and frequently involving transportation to more than one destination.

Class title: Rental of buses and coaches, with operator
Class definition: Rental or operating leasing services of buses or coaches with operator or driver for a period of time, not generally dependent on distance. The renter defines how and when the vehicles will be operated, determining schedules, routes, and other operational considerations.
This class comprises interurban transportation of passengers by rail.
This subclass comprises interurban transportation of passengers by rail.

Class title: Passenger rail transportation services, business class
Class definition: Interurban transportation of passengers by rail, with premium-quality amenities, without sleeping facilities. The fare is not subject to advance purchase requirements or restrictions on exchanges or refunds. Covers the transport of accompanying luggage and other items as well as sales to passengers and bulk purchases by tour operators of seats for resale; exclusive and non-exclusive car usage; and scheduled and non-scheduled services. May include a segment where transportation is by bus. Covers service paid for with a ticket or voucher from a book of tickets, or with a train pass.

Class title: Passenger rail transportation services, economy/discounted economy classes
Class definition: Interurban transportation of passengers by rail, with standard-quality amenities, without sleeping facilities. Food and beverages are available at an extra charge. Covers both economy and discounted economy classes; the latter offers the same amenities as the economy class but contains restrictions such as advance purchase and penalty charges for exchanges and refunds. Covers the transport of accompanying luggage and other items as well as sales to passengers and bulk purchases by tour operators of seats for resale; exclusive and non-exclusive car usage; and scheduled and non-scheduled services. May include a segment where transportation is by bus. Covers service paid for with a ticket or voucher from a book of tickets, or with a train pass.

Class title: Passenger rail transportation services, sleeper class
Class definition: Interurban transportation of passengers by rail, with accommodation in sleeping cars and premium-quality amenities. Covers the transport of accompanying luggage and other items as well as sales to passengers and bulk purchases by tour operators of seats for resale; exclusive and non-exclusive car usage; and scheduled and non-scheduled services. May include a segment where transportation is by bus. Covers service paid for with a ticket or voucher from a book of tickets, or with a train pass.
Hitching of a privately-owned or rented rail car to a train. No services are provided inside the rail car.

This class comprises coastal and Great Lakes fixed route passenger transportation services by water; and other passenger transportation services by water. Rental and leasing services of water passenger transportation vessels with operator or crew are included.

Class title: Water passenger transportation services (except rental with operator)
Class definition: This subclass comprises coastal and Great Lakes fixed route passenger transportation services by water; and other passenger transportation services by water.

Class title: Coastal and Great Lakes fixed route passenger transportation services by water
Class definition: Transportation of passengers by water on fixed routes on coastal waters, the Great Lakes, the St. Lawrence Seaway or deep seas. Covers transportation of motor vehicles, baggage and sporting equipment accompanying passengers as well as optional accommodation such as cabin, berth or reclining sleeper seat.

Class title: Other passenger transportation services by water
Class definition: Transportation of passengers by water on fixed routes within harbours, transportation of passengers by water on fixed routes on inland waters except the Great Lakes and St. Lawrence Seaway, and transportation of passengers by water, not on fixed routes. Service may operate on a regular schedule or on demand. Service that is not on fixed routes often requires advance reservation.

Class title: Rental of water transportation equipment with operator
Class definition: This subclass comprises rental or leasing services of all types of self-propelled passenger vessels for coastal, transoceanic and inland water transport, with operator or crew.

Class title: Rental of water transportation equipment with operator
Class definition: Rental or leasing services of all types of self-propelled passenger vessels for coastal, transoceanic and inland water transport, with operator or crew.
This class comprises scheduled and chartered air passenger transportation services. Rental and leasing of passenger aircraft with operator or crew (wet and damp leasing) are included.

Class title: Scheduled air passenger transportation services (except wet and damp leasing)
Class definition: This subclass comprises transportation of passengers by air on a flight operated on a regular basis according to a published timetable.

Class title: Scheduled air passenger transportation services, domestic
Class definition: Transportation of passengers by air on a domestic scheduled flight.

Class title: Scheduled air passenger transportation services, international
Class definition: Transportation of passengers by air on an international scheduled flight.

This subclass comprises rental and leasing of complete aircraft and crew, for the chartered or non-scheduled transportation of passengers and their accompanying baggage, equipment and supplies. Renters or lessees generally do not have operational control of the flights. Air charter services include air taxi, ad hoc air charter, frequent charter membership and full charter services. Full (public) air charter is a long-term renting of an entire aircraft, usually undertaken by tour operators, that require aircraft on a seasonal basis, but do not have the required infrastructure to operate their own aircraft.

Class title: Air passenger charter transportation services, domestic
Class definition: Rental and leasing of complete aircraft and crew, for the non-scheduled transportation of passengers and their accompanying baggage, equipment and supplies, within Canada. Covers positioning fees, layover fees, and pilot standby fees. Renters or lessees generally do not have operational control of the flights.

Class title: Air passenger charter transportation services, international
Class definition: Rental and leasing of complete aircraft and crew, for the non-scheduled transportation of passengers and their accompanying baggage, equipment and supplies, between Canada and other countries. Covers positioning fees, layover fees, and pilot standby fees. Renters or lessees generally do not have operational control of the flights.

Class title: Rental and leasing of passenger aircraft with operator or crew (except chartering)
Class definition: This subclass comprises rental and leasing services of passenger aircraft or aircraft suitable for passenger and freight (including helicopters) with operator or crew (wet and damp leasing). A ''wet lease'' is a leasing arrangement whereby one "airline" or aircraft operator (the lessor) provides an aircraft, complete crew (''damp lease'' is with only cockpit crew), maintenance, and insurance (ACMI). These services are generally supplied on a time basis and several different destinations are frequently involved. The services may include providing fuel. Renters or lessees generally have operational control of the flights. The period of the rental or lease can go from one month to usually one to two years. Everything less than one month can be considered as ad-hoc charter services.

Class title: Rental and leasing of passenger aircraft with operator or crew (except chartering)
Class definition: Rental and leasing services of passenger aircraft or aircraft suitable for passenger and freight (including helicopters) with operator or crew (wet and damp leasing). A ''wet lease'' is a leasing arrangement whereby one "airline" or aircraft operator (the lessor) provides an aircraft, complete crew (''damp lease'' is with only cockpit crew), maintenance, and insurance (ACMI). These services are generally supplied on a time basis and several different destinations are frequently involved. The services may include providing fuel. Renters or lessees generally have operational control of the flights. The period of the rental or lease can go from one month to usually one to two years. Everything less than one month can be considered as ad-hoc charter services.

This class comprises services which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest by rail, buses and other ground vehicles, water, and air, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. May include commentary, admission to sights or guided visits. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

This subclass comprises services by rail which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment such as steam trains, cog railways and monorails. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. Covers dining trips and theatre trips. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

Services by rail which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment such as steam trains, cog railways and monorails. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. Covers dining trips and theatre trips. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

Class title: Sightseeing services by buses and other ground vehicles
Class definition: This subclass comprises services by buses and other ground vehicles which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. Covers tours that permit clients to get off and board again when they wish. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

Class title: Sightseeing services by buses and other ground vehicles
Class definition: Services by buses and other ground vehicles which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. Covers tours that permit clients to get off and board again when they wish. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

This subclass comprises services by water which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

Services by water which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

This subclass comprises services by air which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

Services by air which take customers to areas of scenic, historical or cultural interest, and/or use vintage or specialized equipment that is an attraction in itself. May include commentary, admission to sights, guided visits, meals or entertainment. These services are short-duration, not involving overnight accommodation.

This group comprises road transportation support services; motor vehicle maintenance and repair services; rail transportation support, maintenance and repair services; water transportation support, maintenance and repair services; air transportation support services; aircraft maintenance and repair services; freight transportation arrangement and customs brokering services; and other transportation support services.

This class comprises services in support of road transportation, such as access to toll roads; towing services; bus terminal services for intercity carriers; drayage services; and snow removal services for roads, highways and bridges.

This subclass comprises services in support of road transportation, such as access to toll roads; towing services; bus terminal services for intercity carriers; drayage services; and snow removal services for roads, highways and bridges.
Access to bridges, tunnels and highways for which a toll is charged.
Towing of road motor vehicles.
Access for carriers to intercity bus stations.
Short movements of truck trailers or containers, by road, between or within terminals, yards or intermodal facilities, or across a border.

Class title: Snow removal services for roads, highways and bridges
Class definition: Snow removal services for roads, highways and bridges.
Support services for road transportation, n.e.c.

Class title: Motor vehicle maintenance and repair services
Class definition: This class comprises maintenance and repair services for automobiles and light trucks; maintenance and repair services for motor homes, travel trailers and campers; and maintenance and repair services for heavy trucks and buses.
