Class definition: Licences for the use of intellectual property from databases, directories and mailing lists to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of stock photos and other literary and artistic works (except software)
Class definition: This subclass comprises licences for the use of intellectual property from stock photos and literary and artistic works, except software, newspapers, periodicals, books, databases, directories and mailing lists, to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of stock photos and other literary and artistic works (except software)
Class definition: Licences for the use of intellectual property from stock photos and literary and artistic works, except software, newspapers, periodicals, books, databases, directories and mailing lists, to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of musical works and sound recordings
Class definition: This class comprises licences for the use of musical works and sound recordings to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of musical works
Class definition: This subclass comprises licences for the use of musical works to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of musical works
Class definition: Licences for the use of musical works to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of sound recordings
Class definition: This subclass comprises licences for the use of sound recordings to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of sound recordings
Class definition: Licences for the use of sound recordings to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of dramatic works, and other copyrighted property n.e.c.
Class definition: This class comprises licences for the use of dramatic works, and other copyrighted property n.e.c. to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of audiovisual works
Class definition: This subclass comprises licences for the use of audiovisual works to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of audiovisual works
Class definition: Licences for the use of audiovisual works to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of other dramatic works, and copyrighted property n.e.c.
Class definition: This subclass comprises licences for the use of dramatic works, except audiovisual works, and of copyrighted property n.e.c. to generate revenues.

Class title: Licensing of rights for commercial use of other dramatic works, and copyrighted property n.e.c.
Class definition: Licences for the use of dramatic works, except audiovisual works, and of copyrighted property n.e.c. to generate revenues.
This class comprises the right to broadcast a sporting event on traditional electronic media and other media rights related to sporting events.
This subclass comprises the right to broadcast a sporting event on traditional electronic media and other media rights related to sporting events.
Rights to broadcast a sporting event on radio or television.
Media rights for sporting events, except broadcasting rights for radio and television.

Class title: Fees for the distribution of television and radio program channels (affiliation payments)
Class definition: This class comprises the right (affiliation payments) for the distribution of a television or audio channel to end users.

Class title: Fees for the distribution of television and radio program channels (affiliation payments)
Class definition: This subclass comprises the right (affiliation payments) for the distribution of a television or audio channel to end users.

Class title: Affiliation payments for the distribution of television channels
Class definition: Rights (affiliation payments) for the distribution of a television channel to end users.

Class title: Affiliation payments for the distribution of audio channels
Class definition: Rights (affiliation payments) for the distribution of an audio channel to end users.

Class title: Telecommunications, broadcasting distribution and related services
Class definition: This group comprises fixed wholesale and retail telecommunications services; fixed wholesale and retail Internet access services; mobile wholesale and retail telecommunications services; cable, satellite, Internet and other fixed or mobile broadcasting distribution services of audiovisual and audio works; and online games, except gambling.
This class comprises fixed wholesale telecommunications and Internet access services, and mobile wholesale telecommunications.

Class title: Fixed wholesale telecommunications services (except Internet access)
Class definition: This subclass comprises the provision of a fixed telecommunications service or facility by a telecommunications service provider to a provider of retail fixed telecommunications services. The purchaser may resell the service or facility to another entity, or use the service or facility to support the services it bills.

Class title: Fixed wholesale telecommunications services (except Internet access)
Class definition: Provision of a fixed telecommunications service or facility by a telecommunications service provider to a provider of retail fixed telecommunications services. The purchaser may resell the service or facility to another entity, or use the service or facility to support the services it bills.
This subclass comprises the provision of fixed Internet access and transport services by a telecommunications service provider to a provider of fixed retail Internet access services.
Provision of fixed Internet access and transport services by a telecommunications service provider to a provider of fixed retail Internet access services.

This subclass comprises the provision of a mobile telecommunications service or facility by a wireless telecommunications service provider to another to exchange traffic and extend service coverage area.
Provision of a mobile telecommunications service or facility by a wireless telecommunications service provider to another to exchange traffic and extend service coverage area.
This class comprises fixed retail telecommunications and Internet access services, and mobile retail telecommunications.

Class title: Fixed retail telecommunications services (except Internet access)
Class definition: This subclass comprises telephone services to end users where calls originate from a device connected to a landline.

Class title: Fixed local and access telecommunications services (except Internet access), at retail
Class definition: A landline-based telephone service that allows end users to make calls within a defined local area and provides access to a long distance network of the customer's choice.

Class title: Fixed long distance telecommunications services (except Internet access), at retail
Class definition: A landline-based telephone service allowing end users to make calls outside a local calling area.
Telecommunications services making use of data protocols to transmit data over a public network.
Telecommunications network segments for the exclusive use of the client on which no control or signalling is performed by the telecommunications service provider.
This subclass comprises the provision of fixed connections (including fixed wireline and wireless) to the Internet to end users.

Provision of fixed connections to the Internet to end users at download speeds not exceeding 64 Kbps. Dial-up Internet access is one of the oldest forms of Internet access technology. It is also referred to as low or narrowband speed Internet access. Narrowband is generally regarded as a category including any connection with a transmission or download speed of up to 1.5 Mbps.

Class title: Fixed high-speed Internet access services, residential
Class definition: Provision of fixed connections to the Internet to residential end users at download speeds generally greater than 256 Kbps. High-speed Internet is also referred to as broadband Internet, with fixed line types such as cable, digital subscriber line (DSL), terrestrial wireless access, direct-to-home satellite access, and fibre optic services. Even though the lowest speed limit for high-speed Internet is set to 256 Kbps in several countries, broadband is generally regarded as a category including any connection with a transmission or download speed of 1.5 Mbps or greater. Connection with download speed from 256 Kbps up to 1.5 Mbps is sometimes referred to as "wideband" or "lite broadband".

Class title: Fixed high-speed Internet access services, non-residential
Class definition: Provision of fixed connections to the Internet to non-residential or business end users at download speeds greater than 256 Kbps. High-speed Internet is also referred to as broadband Internet, with fixed line types such as cable, digital subscriber line (DSL), terrestrial wireless access, direct-to-home satellite access, and fibre optic services. Even though the lowest speed limit for high-speed Internet is set to 256 Kbps in several countries, broadband is generally regarded as a category including any connection with a transmission or download speed of 1.5 Mbps or greater. Connection with download speed from 256 Kbps up to 1.5 Mbps is sometimes referred to as "wideband" or "lite broadband".
This subclass comprises telecommunication services to end users where voice or data communications originate from, or terminate into, a mobile device connected to a wireless network.

Class title: Mobile local and access telecommunications services, at retail
Class definition: A wireless-based telecommunications service that allows end users to make and receive calls within a defined local area and provides access to a long distance network of the customer's choice. Mobile cell phone plans typically bundle voice and text messaging.

Class title: Mobile long distance telecommunications services, at retail
Class definition: Wireless based telecommunications service allowing end users to make calls outside a local calling area.

A service plan providing end users mobile access to text and multimedia messaging, along with access to the Internet through the cellular network. This service is also referred as "wireless mobile Internet access", at retail.
A service that allows a cell phone subscriber to use his or her mobile device while in the service area of another service provider.

Class title: Broadcasting and online games distribution services
Class definition: This class comprises broadcast distribution services of audiovisual and audio works such as television programs, films, videos, sound recordings, via cable, satellite, Internet and other fixed and mobile distribution streams. Also covers distribution services for online games, except gambling, and installation services for connections to broadcasting distribution networks.
This subclass comprises basic television programming packages distribution services, via fixed or mobile devices.

Class title: Basic television programming packages (except online streaming)
Class definition: Providing a basic package of movie and television programming services, basically to a fixed device, except using online streaming, for a monthly subscription fee. Basic packages are any first level programming package that must be purchased before being able to purchase additional programming packages. The basic programming packages are delivered using traditional over-the-air (OTA), cable and satellite television.

Class title: Online streaming of basic programming packages
Class definition: Providing a basic package of movie and television programming services over the Internet, to a fixed or mobile device, using online streaming, for a monthly subscription fee. Basic packages are any first level programming package that must be purchased before being able to purchase additional programming packages.
This subclass comprises discretionary television programming packages distribution services, via fixed or mobile devices.

Providing movie and television programming services, in addition to those included in a basic package, for an additional monthly subscription fee, generally to a fixed device, except using online streaming. This programming service comprises bundles of channels or à la carte channels. The discretionary television programming packages are delivered using traditional cable and satellite television.

Class title: Online streaming of discretionary programming packages
Class definition: Providing movie and television programming services over the Internet, in addition to those included in a basic package, for an additional monthly subscription fee, to a fixed or mobile device, using online streaming. This programming service comprises bundles of channels or à la carte channels.
This subclass comprises pay-per-view services, via fixed or mobile devices. The broadcaster shows a pay-per-view program at the same broadcast time to everyone ordering it.

Providing services which enable subscribers to television programming packages, to watch a specific program (movie or event) at the same broadcast time, generally at a fixed device, for an additional fee, except using online streaming. The pay-per-view services are delivered using traditional cable and satellite television.

Providing services over the Internet which enable subscribers to television programming packages, to watch a specific program (movie or event) at the same broadcast time, on a fixed or mobile device, using online streaming, for an additional fee.

Class title: Television, movie and video on demand services
Class definition: This subclass comprises pay television, movie and other video on demand services (except pay-per-view), via fixed or mobile devices. Subscribers or viewers of video on demand are allowed to choose and watch broadcasts at any time, for a one time fee paid for each individual video that is on demand (transactional video on demand), or for a monthly or annual subscription fee (subscription video on demand) to have unlimited access to television programs, movies and any other types of videos during the time covered by the subscription.

Class title: Television, movie and video on demand (except online streaming)
Class definition: Providing pay television, movie and other video on demand services (except per-pay-view), generally via fixed devices, except using online streaming. Subscribers or viewers to/of video on demand are allowed to choose and watch broadcasts at any time, usually for a one time fee paid for each individual video that is on demand (transactional video on demand). Video on demand services are delivered using traditional cable and satellite television.

Class title: Online on demand streaming of television, movie and video
Class definition: Providing pay television, movie and other video on demand services (except pay-per-view) over the Internet, via fixed or mobile devices, using online streaming. Subscribers or viewers to/of video on demand are allowed to choose and watch broadcasts at any time, usually for a monthly or annual subscription fee (subscription video on demand) to have unlimited access to television programs, movies and any other types of videos during the time covered by the subscription.

Class title: Satellite radio and online audio streaming services
Class definition: This subclass comprises pay satellite radio and online audio (such as music) streaming services.
Pay satellite radio services.

Providing programming services (including self-programming), over the Internet, that comprise a single payment (fee) or a subscription, to a selection of radio shows, music and other audio recordings, streamed to fixed and mobile devices (Internet audio services). Subscribers are allowed to choose and stream contents at any time during the time covered by the payment or subscription.

This subclass comprises provision of various games to be played online, on a subscription or single payment (fee) basis, except gambling. The games are streamed over the Internet to fixed and mobile devices.
Providing various games to be played online, on a subscription or single payment (fee) basis, except gambling. The games are streamed over the Internet to fixed and mobile devices.

Class title: Installation services for connections to broadcasting distribution networks
Class definition: This subclass comprises services of installing cables on the customer premises and/or installing outlets to connect to the program or broadcasting distribution networks.

Class title: Installation services for connections to broadcasting distribution networks
Class definition: Providing installation of cables on the customer premises and/or installing outlets to connect to the program or broadcasting distribution networks.

Class title: Other information technology (IT) and information services
Class definition: This group comprises data processing, hosting and related services, and other information technology (IT) and information services.

Class title: Data processing, hosting, and related services
Class definition: This class comprises services such as website hosting and domain names registration, application provisioning, business process management, infrastructure provisioning, network management, and information and document transformation.

Class title: Website hosting and domain name registration services
Class definition: This subclass comprises the services of providing the infrastructure to host a customer's website and related files in a location that provides connection to the Internet or make their website accessible via the World Wide Web, and domain name registration services.
Services of providing the infrastructure to host a customer's website and related files in a location that provides connection to the Internet or make their website accessible via the World Wide Web.
Services of providing the registration of a domain name for a customer, by certified registrars and authorized resellers or affiliates.

This subclass comprises the provision of leased software applications from a centralized, hosted, and managed computing environment (including cloud), customized to the needs of individual clients or for multi tenant access.

Class title: Application service provisioning (except software as a service, on cloud)
Class definition: Provision of leased software applications from a centralized, hosted, and managed computing environment, customized to the needs of each clients, except software as a service (SaaS), cloud-based or on demand.

Class title: Software as a service, on cloud
Class definition: Provision of rented or leased software applications over the Internet, from a centralized, Internet-hosted, and managed cloud computing multi tenant environment, where all clients can use the same application, on demand, commonly (not exclusively) on a monthly or an annual fee basis. No installation of the application software is needed for the client.

This subclass comprises a service that analyzes the way a business process is conducted, and identifies improvements that can be made by integrating existing and new software services, in order to improve information flows and increase automation of the process.

Services that analyze the way a business process is conducted, and identifies improvements that can be made by integrating existing and new software services, in order to improve information flows and increase automation of the process.

Class title: Other information technology (IT) infrastructure provisioning services
Class definition: This subclass comprises other information technology (IT) hosting or infrastructure provisioning services such as hosting client's application, processing client's data and computer time share.

Class title: Information technology (IT) infrastructure co-location services (except telecommunications facilities)
Class definition: Information technology (IT) infrastructure co-location services, except telecommunications facilities, which provide storage capacity and Internet connections for rental to multiple retail clients.
Services of providing the infrastructure and the management or administration of the storage and back-up of data.
Services of providing the infrastructure and on-going management and administration of data as an organizational resource.

Class title: Video and audio streaming infrastructure provisioning services
Class definition: Services of providing the infrastructure for sending audio and video data over the Internet or providing services to support video and audio streaming over the Internet.

Class title: Other information technology (IT) infrastructure provisioning services, n.e.c.
Class definition: Other information technology (IT) infrastructure provisioning services, n.e.c.

Class title: Information technology (IT) infrastructure and network management services
Class definition: This subclass comprises the service of managing and monitoring a client's information technology (IT) infrastructure including hardware, software and networks.

Services of managing and monitoring communication networks and connected hardware to diagnose networking problems and gather capacity and usage statistics for the administration and fine-tuning of network traffic.
Providing day-to-day management and operation of a client's computer system.
This subclass comprises the provision of technical expertise and equipment to transform information and documents from one format or media to another.

Class title: Imaging and other data capture services
Class definition: Services of converting paper documents into digital or other machine-readable formats. These services generally involve the following components: document preparation; scanning, optical character recognition, and other data capture activities; and the delivery or output of the information captured into a database or a physical medium.
Services of moving data from one storage device to another or from one file format to another.
This class comprises other information services.
This subclass comprises other information services.
Providing access to library resources.
Providing access to archives, and other archive-related services.
Collecting, disseminating or providing access to information, n.e.c.

This group comprises financial system regulatory services; account and cash management products; loans and other credit financing products; investment products; financial planning services and trust products for individuals, businesses, institutions (except unincorporated) and governments; and products supporting financial services.

This class comprises services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies (such as stock exchanges) to regulate financial systems and markets, and the participants in those systems and markets.

This subclass comprises services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies (such as stock exchanges) to regulate securities markets and the participants in securities markets.
Services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies (such as stock exchanges) to regulate securities markets and the participants in securities markets.
This subclass comprises services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies to regulate credit markets and the participants in credit markets.
Services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies to regulate credit markets and the participants in credit markets.
This subclass comprises services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies to regulate insurance markets and the participants in insurance markets.
Services provided by central banks, other government agencies, and self-regulatory bodies to regulate insurance markets and the participants in insurance markets.

This class comprises money management services, provided to customers by means of deposit accounts, such as chequing, savings and time accounts, and specialized cash management services that enable businesses to handle cash, transfer monies, and in general make and receive payments.

This subclass comprises bundled services related to deposit accounts (cheques, account statements, automated banking machine (ABM) transactions, etc.) provided for a flat fee, usually paid monthly. Non-deposit services, such as traveller's cheques, may be included in deposit account service packages.

Bundled services related to deposit accounts (cheques, account statements, automated banking machine (ATM) transactions, etc.) provided for a flat fee, usually paid monthly. Non-deposit services, such as traveller's cheques, may be included in deposit account service packages.
This subclass comprises services related to deposit accounts, sold on an individual basis.
Services related to deposit accounts, sold on an individual basis.
This subclass comprises specialized deposit account and cash management services provided to businesses and government.
Specialized deposit account and cash management services provided to businesses and government.
This subclass comprises issuing documents that can be used as payment instruments.
Issuing documents that can be used as payment instruments.
This subclass comprises exchanging the currency of one country for that of another in small amounts, for a fee or commission.
Exchanging the currency of one country for that of another in small amounts, for a fee or commission.

This class comprises loans that represent the direct lending of funds under legal contract, either unsecured or secured by the assets being financed or by other assets, but without the exchange or the use of securities as collateral.

This subclass comprises loans to businesses. Loans represent the direct lending of funds under legal contract, either unsecured or secured by the assets being financed or by other assets, but without the exchange or the use of securities as collateral.

Loans to businesses. Loans represent the direct lending of funds under legal contract, either unsecured or secured by the assets being financed or by other assets, but without the exchange or the use of securities as collateral.
This subclass comprises loans to government.
Loans to government.
This subclass comprises loans to households.
Mortgage loans provided to owner-occupiers, secured by residential real property.
Loans and lines of credit secured by the equity of a borrower's residence.

Class title: Secured home loans (except residential mortgage and home equity loans) to households
Class definition: Secured or guaranteed home loans to households, except residential mortgage and home equity loans.
Loans to households for purchasing automobiles and other vehicles, secured by the vehicle.

Class title: Other secured consumer loans to households, n.e.c.
Class definition: Other secured loans to households, n.e.c.
Loans and lines of credit, not secured by collateral, for personal uses.
This class comprises credit card services; factoring; financial leasing; and sales financing.

This subclass comprises the provision of lines of credit to credit card holders, and credit card processing services to merchants, that together enable credit cards to be accepted as a means of payment.

Class title: Credit card cardholder products for businesses and government
Class definition: Provision of a revolving line of credit to business and government holders of credit cards, allowing them to purchase goods and services from merchants who accept their card. Credit granted through credit cards may be unsecured, or secured by a deposit held by the card issuer.

Class title: Credit card cardholder products to consumers
Class definition: Provision of a revolving line of credit to consumer holders of credit cards, allowing them to purchase goods and services from merchants who accept their card. Credit granted through credit cards may be unsecured, or secured by a deposit held by the card issuer.
Credit card transaction processing services provided by processors and banks to merchant account holders.
Services provided by credit card associations to issuing banks.

This subclass comprises the provision of financing to a business from the sale of its accounts receivable to a third party, known as a factor. Normally, the factor assumes the full risk of collection, including credit losses.
Financing provided to a business from the sale of its accounts receivable to a third party, known as a factor. Normally, the factor assumes the full risk of collection, including credit losses.

This subclass comprises leases in which the lessor is providing a financial service to enable the lessee to enjoy the benefits of ownership of the leased asset. A lessee has the option of purchasing the machinery and equipment after the lease term has been completed, at an agreed price. With a finance lease the equipment appears on the lessee's balance sheet, as it is viewed as a purchase. Also known as capital lease.

Motor vehicle leases in which the lessor is providing a financial service to enable the lessee to enjoy the benefits of ownership of the leased asset. A lessee has the option of purchasing the motor vehicle after the lease term has been completed, at an agreed price. With a finance lease the motor vehicle appears on the lessee's balance sheet, as it is viewed as a purchase.

Leases (except for motor vehicles) in which the lessor is providing a financial service to enable the lessee to enjoy the benefits of ownership of the leased asset. A lessee has the option of purchasing the machinery and equipment after the lease term has been completed, at an agreed price. With a finance lease the equipment appears on the lessee's balance sheet, as it is viewed as a purchase.
This subclass comprises the provision of credit by means of conditional sales contracts.
Providing credit by means of conditional sales contracts for purchases by businesses.
Providing credit by means of conditional sales contracts for purchases by consumers.

This class comprises financing services related to trading and dealing in securities which generally involve the use of securities as collateral or as the lent instrument, as well as other credit financing products, n.e.c.

This subclass comprises financing services related to trading and dealing in securities which generally involve the use of securities as collateral or as the lent instrument, as well as other credit financing products, n.e.c.
Collateralized lending of securities, to be returned on a specific date or on demand, paid for by fees based on the value of the loaned securities.
The sale of a security (often Treasury Bills) to a counterparty for cash with an agreement to repurchase it at a fixed price on a specified future date.
Provision of credit by means other than loans, credit cards, factoring, leasing, instalment credit products, and financing related to securities lending and repurchase agreements.
This class comprises securities origination products; brokering and dealing of financial instruments; and brokerage correspondent products.

This subclass comprises assisting the issuers of securities (businesses and government) in creating their securities and in having them distributed to the investing public. The service may involve advising the issuer; purchasing securities from the issuer and selling them (underwriting); or acting as an agent in marketing the securities.

Assisting the issuers of securities (businesses and government) in creating their securities and in having them distributed to the investing public. The service may involve advising the issuer; purchasing securities from the issuer and selling them (underwriting); or acting as an agent in marketing the securities.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of money market instruments
Class definition: This subclass comprises brokering and dealing money market instruments, which are fixed-rate of return debt instruments that mature within one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, negotiable certificates of deposit
Class definition: Brokering and dealing negotiable certificates of deposit, with a term of one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, commercial paper issued by financial institutions
Class definition: Brokering and dealing commercial paper issued by financial institutions, with a term of one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, commercial paper issued by non-financial institutions
Class definition: Brokering and dealing commercial paper issued by non-financial institutions, with a term of one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, bankers' acceptances
Class definition: Brokering and dealing bankers' acceptances, with a term of one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, Treasury bills
Class definition: Brokering and dealing Treasury bills, with a term of one year or less.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, other money market instruments
Class definition: Brokering and dealing money market instruments other than commercial paper, bankers' acceptances, negotiable certificates of deposit, or Treasury bills.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of other debt instruments
Class definition: This subclass comprises brokering and dealing debt instruments other than money market instruments.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, corporate bonds and asset-backed securities
Class definition: Brokering and dealing medium- and long-term corporate notes and bonds, and asset-backed securities.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, national government notes and bonds
Class definition: Brokering and dealing medium- and long-term bonds issued by the Government of Canada.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, provincial and local government notes and bonds
Class definition: Brokering and dealing medium- and long-term bonds issued by provincial and local governments.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, foreign government notes and bonds
Class definition: Brokering and dealing notes and bonds issued by foreign governments.
This subclass comprises brokering and dealing equity securities.
Brokering and dealing equity securities.
This subclass comprises brokering and dealing in derivative instruments, which are contracts whose value is based on the value of an underlying entity.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, futures contracts, exchange-traded
Class definition: Brokering and dealing futures contracts on exchanges.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, option contracts, exchange-traded
Class definition: Brokering and dealing option contracts on exchanges.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, forward contracts, traded over-the-counter
Class definition: Brokering and dealing forward contracts over-the-counter.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, swaps, traded over-the-counter
Class definition: Brokering and dealing swap contracts over-the-counter.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, option contracts, traded over-the-counter
Class definition: Brokering and dealing option contracts over-the-counter.

Class title: Brokering and dealing products, other derivatives contracts, traded over-the-counter
Class definition: Brokering and dealing derivative contracts, other than forward, swap or option contracts, over-the-counter.

Class title: Foreign currency wholesale brokering and dealing
Class definition: This subclass comprises brokering and dealing foreign currencies, on a wholesale basis.

Class title: Foreign currency wholesale brokering and dealing
Class definition: Brokering and dealing foreign currencies, on a wholesale basis.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of investment company securities
Class definition: This subclass comprises brokering and dealing investment company securities.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of investment company securities
Class definition: Brokering and dealing investment company securities.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of other financial instruments
Class definition: This subclass comprises brokering and dealing other financial instruments.

Class title: Brokering and dealing of other financial instruments
Class definition: Brokering and dealing other financial instruments.

This subclass comprises the service consisting of one broker-dealer carrying out trades on behalf of another, where the first broker-dealer has access to a particular securities exchange and the other does not.
Service consisting of one broker-dealer carrying out trades on behalf of another, where the first broker-dealer has access to a particular securities exchange and the other does not.

Class title: Personal trust and financial planning services
Class definition: This class comprises trust services and financial planning and investment management services intended for private individuals.

Class title: Personal trust and financial planning services
Class definition: This subclass comprises trust services and financial planning and investment management services intended for private individuals.

Services to establish and administer trusts, under which a trustee holds legal title to property belonging to another, for the benefit of a beneficiary. Trusts are defined by an agreement, contract, declaration in a will, or order of a court.

Class title: Personal financial planning and investment management services
Class definition: Financial planning and investment management services for individuals.

Class title: Trust and financial planning services for businesses, institutions, and government
Class definition: This class comprises trust services and financial planning and investment management services for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments.

Class title: Trust and financial planning services for businesses, institutions, and government
Class definition: This subclass comprises trust services and financial planning and investment management services for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments.

Class title: Trust services for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments
Class definition: Services to establish and administer trusts for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments.

Class title: Financial planning and investment management services for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments
Class definition: Financial planning and investment management services for businesses, institutions (except unincorporated), and governments.

Class title: Tax planning and consulting services for businesses (except unincorporated) and governments
Class definition: Tax planning and consulting services for businesses (except unincorporated) and governments.
This class comprises management of financial market and clearing products; automated clearing house products; and other products supporting financial services.

Class title: Management of financial market and clearing services
Class definition: This subclass comprises the provision of an infrastructure for trading securities and commodity contracts; and clearing and settlement services for securities, commodities contracts, and payments. Covers trades executed on exchanges or over-the-counter, and clearing and settlement services for those trades.
Clearing and settling payments for financial transactions other than trades of securities and commodity contracts.

Class title: Security and commodity contract trade execution, clearing and settlement services
Class definition: Executing, clearing and settling trades of securities and commodity contracts and other financial instruments.

Class title: Services of access to security and commodity contract trade execution and clearing systems
Class definition: Providing broker-dealers with access to securities or commodity contract trading systems, whether live floor exchanges or electronic systems.

Class title: Security and commodity contract exchange and clearing house listing services
Class definition: Listing securities and other financial instruments on trading, clearing and settlement systems.

Class title: Other management of financial market and clearing services
Class definition: Providing support services for trading, clearing and settling securities and commodities contracts and financial payments, n.e.c.
This subclass comprises automated funds credit and debit clearing and settlement services.
Automated funds credit and debit clearing and settlement services.
This subclass comprises loan servicing; automated banking machine (ABM) operation products; and other miscellaneous products supporting financial services.

Loan servicing entails the processing of payments of principal and interest, the maintenance of associated accounts such as escrow accounts for the payment of taxes and insurance, and the provision of loan information.
Use of automated banking machines (ABMs) not associated with the user's financial institution.

Class title: Other miscellaneous products supporting financial services
Class definition: Products supporting financial services, n.e.c.
This group comprises pension and annuity products; and life insurance products.

This class comprises underwriting services of plans which provide income payments at regular intervals to individuals or members of groups. Plans may require a single contribution or a series of contributions; may be compulsory or optional; may have nominal benefits determined in advance or dependent on the market value of aspects supporting the plan; and, if related to employment, may or may not be portable with a change in employment. The duration of the period during which benefits are paid may be fixed in terms of a minimum or maximum; there may or may not be survivors' benefits.
